        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 1:31PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Independence Lake, or 8 miles west of Stampede Reservoir, moving east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stampede Reservoir, Boca Reservoir, Independence Lake, Hobart Mills,
Ca 89 At Nevada-Sierra Co Line, Upper Little Truckee Campground, Boca
Rest Campground, and Logger Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
